The Twin VHX-220 architecture is intended as a modular propulsion core that
can be replicated according to application requirements.

Possible configurations include:

• Single Module (1×)

• Twin Module (2×)

• Quad Module (4×)

• Heavy-Duty Multi-Module Arrays

Performance scales primarily through increased installed propulsion capacity,
with practical limits governed by available electrical power, thermal
management, structural design, and control-system complexity.

